description:
Issue: NI Internal User n7gonza is having an issue with PayApp. 

Business Impact: Please fix this payapp  Payment Application Non-Retainage: 3-1-1300057910-527395698

Root Cause: When we validate pay app postings for associated PO in SAP system, we can see previous pay app record (2-0-1300057910-519083374) in line 3 (PLANOS )was posted twice by mistake. That's a reason , current pay app is getting failed to interface with SAP because already amount for this line 3 was paid for GR .

Resolution: •	Please reverse this incorrect duplicate posting in SAP system. And then if we resend the pay app again from Tririga , it should post (GR and IR) successfully without any issues.

                                                                        (OR)

•	Please create IR posting ( Invoice ) alone in SAP system for this line 3. Then , we can complete the pay app record in Tririga.
 

Next Step: Support team to start investigation

Work Summary::

6/2- Acknowledged
6/2- Analysis in progress
6/3- Provided detailed analysis and its solution to user to be follow. Awaiting user response on this.

short_description: US - MMIP - Extension of article to all sites and on accounting
description:
From: Dipika Mohapatra 
Sent: Tuesday, March 17, 2020 4:30 AM
To: AccentureGBS.ISM.All <accenturegbs.ism.all@email.wal-mart.com>; FPMO Support <fpmost1@wal-mart.com>
Cc: Haya Fatima <Haya.Fatima0@walmart.com>; Neeraj Aryan <Neeraj.Kumararyan@walmart.com>; Sajal Dixit <Sajal.Dixit@walmartlabs.com>; Deepika Modemreddy <Deepika.Modemreddy@walmart.com>; TFATC <TFATC171@wal-mart.com>; Manjunath Somashekara <M.Somashekara@walmart.com>
Subject: RE: Extension of article to all sites and on accounting - Background job 

Hi Team,

During analysis of automated job for article listing I came through below job which is cancelled.

Can you have a look why the below job is cancelled in PR4 from 13th March and not started again.

 
Thanks,
Dipika

From: Sajal Dixit <Sajal.Dixit@walmartlabs.com> 
Sent: Monday, March 16, 2020 11:16 AM
To: Dipika Mohapatra <Dipika.Mohapatra@walmart.com>
Cc: Haya Fatima <Haya.Fatima0@walmart.com>; Neeraj Aryan <Neeraj.Kumararyan@walmart.com>; Deepika Modemreddy <Deepika.Modemreddy@walmart.com>; Manjunath Somashekara <M.Somashekara@walmart.com>
Subject: Extension of article to all sites and on accounting - Background job 

Hi Dipika,
As discussed, we should not use WSM3 in production to extend all US or Canada sites manually. 

What is happening currently:
1.	At the time of article creation, article only extend to few assorts (13 out of total 34 for US, 3 out of total 7 for Canada). It doesn't extend to all assorts (including all US sites) until we run WSM3 manually.
2.	Whenever we get request to extend article to all sites, we run WSM3 with job variant "CTHORNB – Variant for manual listings US" and "US_WSM3_CA_NEW – Variant for manual listing Canada" for US and Canada respectively.
3.	Most of the times, few sites left from this manual extension. After checking listing of article that article has all available assorts but still few sites are left on which it is not extended, we try to add specific sites into assorts by "WSOA6 – Assortment Maintenance tool"
4.	Since last 1 month, we are getting request that article has not been maintained on accounting even after listing to all US sites from WSM3 manually.

We should check the background job which maintain articles to all sites after article creation. Ideally it should extend article to all sites automatically without running WSM3 manually and also should maintain on specific store or DC for which accounting view is a part of. 

Please let me know your thoughts on it. 

Regards,
Sajal Dixit | Analyst
IPS Tech
Global Business Services
+91-8587983821 | sajal.dixit@walmartlabs.com
